    "details": {
      "biography": "<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">For their own equipment, Polop prefer to use living </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">sea organisms sorceled into suitable weapons and scaly </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">armor. Their &ldquo;spitters&rdquo; cough bone darts that function as </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">thrown light spears, and the spears and slave-taking clubs </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">they use are of a living coral. The weapons of their leaders </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">sweat a venom that forces a victim that is struck to make </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">a Physical save or lose their next turn&rsquo;s Main Action. Two </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">failed saving throws in the same scene means the victim </span><span style=\"color: #191813;\">is paralyzed for the remainder of the scene.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Two attacks per round. Add 3 to weapon damage and shock values.</span></p>",
